---
import StudyLayout from '../../../layouts/StudyLayout.astro';
const bodyHtml = `<header>
    <div class="kicker">// CCA-F FIELD MANUAL : DOMAIN 1.1</div>
    <h1>The Agentic<br>Loop Lifecycle</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A build exercise. First we watch a single call hit a dead end. Then you assemble the loop one step at a time and watch it come alive.<span class="blink"></span></p>
  </header>

  <!-- GOAL -->
  <div class="goal">
    <span class="tag">▶ THE GOAL</span>
    <p class="big">By the end of this page you will <b>build the agentic loop</b>: the machinery that turns a single dead-end call into a model that can use tools and keep working until the task is done.</p>
    <p class="goal-sub">You will assemble it one step at a time and watch it run.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- PART 1: WITHOUT THE LOOP -->
  <section id="without">
    <div class="sec-num">PART 01</div>
    <h2>Without the Loop</h2>
    <p class="lead">Here is the instinct every new builder has: call the model once, get the answer, done. Watch what happens when the model wants a tool.</p>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="fname">single_shot.py</span>
      </div>
<pre><code><span class="k">from</span> dotenv <span class="k">import</span> load_dotenv
<span class="k">import</span> anthropic

<span class="c"># pull ANTHROPIC_API_KEY out of .env so the SDK can read it</span>
<span class="f">load_dotenv</span>()

client <span class="k">=</span> anthropic.<span class="f">Anthropic</span>()

tools <span class="k">=</span> [{
    <span class="s">"name"</span>: <span class="s">"get_order_status"</span>,
    <span class="s">"description"</span>: <span class="s">"Look up the status of a customer order by ID."</span>,
    <span class="s">"input_schema"</span>: {
        <span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"object"</span>,
        <span class="s">"properties"</span>: {<span class="s">"order_id"</span>: {<span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"string"</span>}},
        <span class="s">"required"</span>: [<span class="s">"order_id"</span>],
    },
}]

resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(
    model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,
    max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>,
    tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,
    messages<span class="k">=</span>[{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: <span class="s">"Where is order A-4471?"</span>}],
)

<span class="c"># We just... look at what came back.</span>
<span class="f">print</span>(resp.stop_reason)   <span class="c"># -> "tool_use"</span>
<span class="f">print</span>(resp.content)       <span class="c"># -> [ToolUseBlock(name="get_order_status", ...)]</span></code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="fail">
      <div class="label">// DEAD END</div>
      <ul>
        <li>The model returned a <span class="glow-mg">request</span> to call <code class="glow-lm">get_order_status</code>, not an answer.</li>
        <li>The tool <span class="glow-mg">never ran</span>. No code executed the request. The model cannot run it itself.</li>
        <li>The result <span class="glow-mg">never went back</span>. The model still has no idea where order A-4471 is.</li>
        <li><code>stop_reason</code> is <span class="glow-lm">"tool_use"</span>, which is the model saying <i>"your turn, run this, then come back."</i> Nobody came back.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p>A single call is structurally incapable of finishing a tool-using task. The fix is not a bigger prompt or a smarter model. The fix is a <span class="glow-cy">loop</span>, and the next section explains why.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- PART 2: WHY THE LOOP EXISTS -->
  <section id="why">
    <div class="sec-num">PART 02</div>
    <h2>Why the Loop Exists</h2>
    <p class="lead">You just watched a single call hit a wall. Here is the idea that fixes it, and the four pillars the loop is built on.</p>

    <div class="concept">
      <span class="tag">★ THE CORE IDEA</span>
      <p class="big">The model <b>never executes tools</b>. It only <b>requests</b> them. The loop is the developer-owned machinery that runs the request, returns the result, and asks the model what to do next, repeating until the model says it is done.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="lead">Four pillars hold that idea up. Keep them in view as you build, because every step in the next section is one of these made real:</p>

    <div class="pillars">
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="n">01</div>
        <h3 class="glow-mg">A single call is a dead end</h3>
        <p>One <code>messages.create()</code> returns a tool request and stops. With no loop, the tool never runs and the task never completes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="n">02</div>
        <h3 class="glow-cy">stop_reason owns termination</h3>
        <p>The loop runs while <code>stop_reason == "tool_use"</code> and exits on <code>end_turn</code>. You never read the model's text to decide if it finished.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="n">03</div>
        <h3 class="glow-lm">The result must go back</h3>
        <p>Each <code>tool_result</code> is appended to <code>messages</code> and sent again, giving the model the info it asked for. One round-trip per iteration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="n">04</div>
        <h3 style="color:var(--neon-amber)">The cap is a backstop</h3>
        <p>The iteration limit catches runaway loops. It is not the brake. Healthy termination is always <code>end_turn</code>, never the cap.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PART 3: BUILD -->
  <section id="build">
    <div class="sec-num">PART 03</div>
    <h2>Build It, Step by Step</h2>
    <p class="lead">Click <b class="glow-lm">ADD STEP</b> to assemble the loop one piece at a time. Watch the code panel grow and read why each piece exists. Four of the steps make one of the pillars real; the other two are the plumbing that holds them together.</p>

    <div class="builder">
      <!-- STEPS -->
      <div class="steps-col" id="stepsCol">
        <div class="step" data-step="1">
          <span class="chk">[OK]</span>
          <div class="sn">STEP 1</div>
          <h4>Seed the conversation</h4>
          <p>Start a <code>messages</code> list with the user request. This list is the loop's memory. It grows by one round-trip each pass.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step" data-step="2">
          <span class="chk">[OK]</span>
          <div class="sn">STEP 2</div>
          <h4>Open the loop &nbsp;<span style="color:var(--neon-magenta)">[Pillar 01]</span></h4>
          <p>A single <code>create()</code> call returns a tool request and stops, the dead end from Part 01. Wrap the call in <code>while True</code> so it can run again. Each pass sends the <i>entire</i> growing message list, never just the latest turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step" data-step="3">
          <span class="chk">[OK]</span>
          <div class="sn">STEP 3</div>
          <h4>Inspect stop_reason &nbsp;<span style="color:var(--neon-cyan)">[Pillar 02]</span></h4>
          <p>Append the model's reply, then branch on <code>stop_reason</code>. If it is not <code>"tool_use"</code>, the model is done. Break. Never parse the text.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step" data-step="4">
          <span class="chk">[OK]</span>
          <div class="sn">STEP 4</div>
          <h4>Execute the requested tool</h4>
          <p>Pull each <code>tool_use</code> block, run the real function it names, and capture the output. <i>This</i> is the step the model physically cannot do for itself.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step" data-step="5">
          <span class="chk">[OK]</span>
          <div class="sn">STEP 5</div>
          <h4>Feed the result back &nbsp;<span style="color:var(--neon-lime)">[Pillar 03]</span></h4>
          <p>Append a <code>tool_result</code> message keyed to the request's <code>id</code>. Now the loop sends again, and the model finally has its answer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step" data-step="6">
          <span class="chk">[OK]</span>
          <div class="sn">STEP 6</div>
          <h4>Add the backstop &nbsp;<span style="color:var(--neon-amber)">[Pillar 04]</span></h4>
          <p>Cap total iterations so a misbehaving model cannot loop forever. This is a safety net, not the exit. The real exit is <code>end_turn</code> in Step 3.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- LIVE PANEL -->
      <div class="panel-col">
        <div class="code live-code">
          <div class="code-bar">
            <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span><span class="dot g"></span>
            <span class="fname">agent_loop.py &nbsp;<span id="lineCount" style="color:var(--neon-cyan)"></span></span>
          </div>
          <pre><code id="liveCode"><span class="empty-state c"># Empty. Click ADD STEP to begin assembling the loop...</span></code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="controls">
          <button id="addBtn">+ Add Step 1</button>
          <button id="resetBtn" class="ghost">↺ Reset</button>
          <span class="progress" id="progress">0 / 6</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PART 3: COMPLETE -->
  <section id="complete">
    <div class="sec-num">PART 04</div>
    <h2>The Assembled Loop</h2>
    <p class="lead">The entire file, top to bottom: imports and client setup, the tool plus the real function behind it, and the assembled loop, seed → call → check → execute → feed back, repeating until <code class="glow-lm">end_turn</code>. Drop in your <code>.env</code> and it runs.</p>

    <div class="code">
      <div class="code-bar">
        <span class="dot r"></span><span class="dot y"></span><span class="dot g"></span>
        <span class="fname">agent_loop.py &nbsp;[complete]</span>
      </div>
<pre><code><span class="k">from</span> dotenv <span class="k">import</span> load_dotenv
<span class="k">import</span> anthropic

<span class="c"># pull ANTHROPIC_API_KEY out of .env so the SDK can read it</span>
<span class="f">load_dotenv</span>()

client <span class="k">=</span> anthropic.<span class="f">Anthropic</span>()

tools <span class="k">=</span> [{
    <span class="s">"name"</span>: <span class="s">"get_order_status"</span>,
    <span class="s">"description"</span>: <span class="s">"Look up the status of a customer order by ID."</span>,
    <span class="s">"input_schema"</span>: {
        <span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"object"</span>,
        <span class="s">"properties"</span>: {<span class="s">"order_id"</span>: {<span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"string"</span>}},
        <span class="s">"required"</span>: [<span class="s">"order_id"</span>],
    },
}]


<span class="c"># the real function behind the tool, the model cannot run this itself</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="f">get_order_status</span>(order_id):
    <span class="c"># in a real app this would hit your database or an API</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="s">f"Order {order_id}: shipped, arriving Tuesday."</span>


<span class="c"># route each tool name to its Python function</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="f">execute_tool</span>(name, tool_input):
    <span class="k">if</span> name <span class="k">==</span> <span class="s">"get_order_status"</span>:
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="f">get_order_status</span>(<span class="k">**</span>tool_input)
    <span class="k">raise</span> <span class="f">ValueError</span>(<span class="s">f"Unknown tool: {name}"</span>)


<span class="k">def</span> <span class="f">run_agent</span>(user_message, max_iterations<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">10</span>):
    messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]

    <span class="c"># Pillar 04: backstop, not the brake</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> _ <span class="k">in</span> <span class="f">range</span>(max_iterations):
        resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(
            model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,
            max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>,
            tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,
            <span class="c"># send the FULL growing history</span>
            messages<span class="k">=</span>messages,
        )
        messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"assistant"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: resp.content})

        <span class="c"># Pillar 02: stop_reason owns the exit</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> resp.stop_reason <span class="k">!=</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
            <span class="c"># end_turn -> the model is done</span>
            <span class="k">return</span> resp

        tool_results <span class="k">=</span> []
        <span class="k">for</span> block <span class="k">in</span> resp.content:
            <span class="k">if</span> block.type <span class="k">==</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
                <span class="c"># YOU run it</span>
                output <span class="k">=</span> <span class="f">execute_tool</span>(block.name, block.input)
                tool_results.<span class="f">append</span>({
                    <span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"tool_result"</span>,
                    <span class="c"># key it to the request</span>
                    <span class="s">"tool_use_id"</span>: block.id,
                    <span class="s">"content"</span>: output,
                })

        <span class="c"># Pillar 03: feed back</span>
        messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: tool_results})

    <span class="c"># backstop fired</span>
    <span class="k">raise</span> <span class="f">RuntimeError</span>(<span class="s">"Hit iteration cap without end_turn"</span>)


<span class="c"># kick it off</span>
<span class="k">if</span> __name__ <span class="k">==</span> <span class="s">"__main__"</span>:
    final <span class="k">=</span> <span class="f">run_agent</span>(<span class="s">"Where is order A-4471?"</span>)
    <span class="f">print</span>(final.content[<span class="n">0</span>].text)</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DIAGRAM -->
  <section id="cycle">
    <div class="sec-num">PART 05</div>
    <h2>The Lifecycle, At a Glance</h2>
    <p class="lead">One full pass through the loop. The arrow back to the top is the whole point: it is what a single call is missing.</p>

    <div class="diagram">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 760 360" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="'JetBrains Mono',monospace">
        <defs>
          <marker id="arrow" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="10" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#19f0ff"/>
          </marker>
          <marker id="arrowMg" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="10" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#ff2bd6"/>
          </marker>
        </defs>

        <!-- nodes -->
        <g>
          <rect x="40" y="40" width="180" height="64" rx="4" fill="#120a24" stroke="#19f0ff" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="130" y="68" fill="#19f0ff" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">CALL MODEL</text>
          <text x="130" y="86" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">messages.create()</text>
        </g>

        <g>
          <rect x="290" y="40" width="180" height="64" rx="4" fill="#120a24" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="380" y="68" fill="#9dff3c" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">CHECK stop_reason</text>
          <text x="380" y="86" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">tool_use? end_turn?</text>
        </g>

        <g>
          <rect x="540" y="40" width="180" height="64" rx="4" fill="#0a0612" stroke="#ff3b6b" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="630" y="68" fill="#ff3b6b" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">end_turn → EXIT</text>
          <text x="630" y="86" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">return to caller</text>
        </g>

        <g>
          <rect x="290" y="240" width="180" height="64" rx="4" fill="#120a24" stroke="#ffb627" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="380" y="268" fill="#ffb627" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">EXECUTE TOOL</text>
          <text x="380" y="286" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">get_order_status()</text>
        </g>

        <g>
          <rect x="40" y="240" width="180" height="64" rx="4" fill="#120a24" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <text x="130" y="268" fill="#ff2bd6" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700">APPEND result</text>
          <text x="130" y="286" fill="#7e6fa8" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">tool_result → messages</text>
        </g>

        <!-- arrows -->
        <line x1="220" y1="72" x2="284" y2="72" stroke="#19f0ff" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <line x1="470" y1="72" x2="534" y2="72" stroke="#19f0ff" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <text x="500" y="60" fill="#ff3b6b" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">done</text>

        <!-- check -> execute (tool_use) -->
        <line x1="380" y1="104" x2="380" y2="234" stroke="#9dff3c" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrow)"/>
        <text x="430" y="175" fill="#9dff3c" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle">tool_use</text>

        <!-- execute -> append -->
        <line x1="290" y1="272" x2="226" y2="272" stroke="#ffb627" stroke-width="1.5" marker-end="url(#arrowMg)"/>

        <!-- append -> call model (THE LOOP) -->
        <path d="M130,240 L130,104" stroke="#ff2bd6" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6 4" marker-end="url(#arrowMg)"/>
        <text x="130" y="180" fill="#ff2bd6" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="700" transform="rotate(-90 130 175)" style="letter-spacing:1px">THE LOOP ↺</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RECAP -->
  <section id="recap">
    <div class="recap">
      <h3>// LOCK IT IN</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><b>stop_reason is the only exit signal.</b> Loop while <code>"tool_use"</code>, leave on <code>end_turn</code>. Reading the model's natural language to guess "is it finished?" is the classic anti-pattern.</li>
        <li><b>The model requests, you execute.</b> The single biggest mental flip: Claude never runs a tool. It emits a structured request, and your loop is what makes that request real and returns the answer.</li>
        <li><b>The iteration cap is a backstop, never the brake.</b> A healthy task ends on <code>end_turn</code>. If your loop routinely exits by hitting the cap, something upstream is broken.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    AGENTIC LOOP LIFECYCLE // build exercise // no code execution, study artifact only<span class="blink"></span>
  </footer>`;
---

<StudyLayout title="The Agentic Loop Lifecycle">
  <div class="wrap" set:html={bodyHtml}></div>
</StudyLayout>

<style is:global>
/* scanline + grain atmosphere */
  
  

  .wrap{
    max-width:1080px;
    margin:0 auto;
    padding:0 24px 120px;
    position:relative;
    z-index:1;
  }

  /* ---------- HEADER ---------- */
  header{
    padding:90px 0 50px;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--panel-line);
    position:relative;
  }
  .kicker{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.5rem;
    color:var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing:4px;
    text-shadow:0 0 12px rgba(25,240,255,0.6);
    margin-bottom:10px;
  }
  h1{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:clamp(3rem,9vw,7rem);
    line-height:0.92;
    color:var(--neon-magenta);
    text-shadow:
      0 0 18px rgba(255,43,214,0.7),
      4px 4px 0 rgba(25,240,255,0.35);
    letter-spacing:2px;
    text-transform:uppercase;
  }
  .subtitle{
    margin-top:22px;
    max-width:640px;
    color:var(--text-dim);
    font-size:0.95rem;
  }
  
  

  /* ---------- KEY CONCEPT BANNER ---------- */
  .concept{
    margin:48px 0;
    border:1px solid var(--neon-magenta);
    background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,43,214,0.06), rgba(255,43,214,0.01));
    padding:28px 30px;
    box-shadow:0 0 30px rgba(255,43,214,0.12), inset 0 0 30px rgba(255,43,214,0.04);
    position:relative;
  }
  .concept .tag{
    position:absolute;
    top:-11px;
    left:24px;
    background:var(--bg-deep);
    padding:0 10px;
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.2rem;
    color:var(--neon-magenta);
    letter-spacing:3px;
    text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(255,43,214,0.7);
  }
  .concept .big{
    font-size:1.15rem;
    color:#fff;
    line-height:1.5;
    font-weight:700;
  }
  .concept .big b{color:var(--neon-cyan);text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(25,240,255,0.5);}

  /* ---------- GOAL BANNER (top) ---------- */
  .goal{
    margin:48px 0;
    border:1px solid var(--neon-cyan);
    background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(25,240,255,0.06), rgba(25,240,255,0.01));
    padding:28px 30px;
    box-shadow:0 0 30px rgba(25,240,255,0.12), inset 0 0 30px rgba(25,240,255,0.04);
    position:relative;
  }
  .goal .tag{
    position:absolute;top:-11px;left:24px;background:var(--bg-deep);padding:0 10px;
    font-family:var(--crt);font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--neon-cyan);letter-spacing:3px;
    text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(25,240,255,0.7);
  }
  .goal .big{font-size:1.15rem;color:#fff;line-height:1.5;font-weight:700;}
  .goal .big b{color:var(--neon-lime);text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(157,255,60,0.5);}
  .goal-sub{margin-top:8px;font-size:0.86rem;color:var(--text-dim);}

  /* ---------- SECTION ---------- */
  section{padding:64px 0 0;}
  .sec-num{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.4rem;
    color:var(--neon-lime);
    letter-spacing:3px;
    text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(157,255,60,0.5);
  }
  h2{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.4rem);
    color:var(--text);
    text-transform:uppercase;
    letter-spacing:1px;
    margin:6px 0 18px;
    line-height:1;
  }
  .lead{color:var(--text-dim);max-width:680px;margin-bottom:14px;font-size:0.95rem;}
  p{font-size:0.95rem;}
  p + p{margin-top:12px;}

  /* ---------- PILLARS ---------- */
  .pillars{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr));
    gap:16px;
    margin-top:30px;
  }
  .pillar{
    border:1px solid var(--panel-line);
    background:var(--panel);
    padding:20px;
    position:relative;
    transition:border-color .2s, box-shadow .2s, transform .2s;
  }
  .pillar:hover{border-color:var(--neon-cyan);box-shadow:0 0 20px rgba(25,240,255,0.15);transform:translateY(-3px);}
  .pillar .n{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.8rem;
    color:var(--neon-amber);
    text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(255,182,39,0.5);
  }
  .pillar h3{font-size:0.95rem;color:#fff;margin:4px 0 8px;}
  .pillar p{font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text-dim);}
  .pillar code{color:var(--neon-lime);}

  /* ---------- CODE BLOCKS ---------- */
  .code{
    border:1px solid var(--panel-line);
    background:var(--bg);
    margin:22px 0;
    position:relative;
    box-shadow:0 0 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  }
  .code-bar{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:8px;
    padding:9px 14px;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--panel-line);
    background:var(--panel);
  }
  .dot{width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:50%;}
  .dot.r{background:var(--danger);box-shadow:0 0 8px var(--danger);}
  .dot.y{background:var(--neon-amber);box-shadow:0 0 8px var(--neon-amber);}
  .dot.g{background:var(--neon-lime);box-shadow:0 0 8px var(--neon-lime);}
  .code-bar .fname{
    margin-left:8px;
    font-size:0.78rem;
    color:var(--text-dim);
    letter-spacing:1px;
  }
  .code pre{
    margin:0;
    padding:20px 22px;
    overflow-x:auto;
    font-size:0.84rem;
    line-height:1.65;
    tab-size:4;
  }
  .code pre code{font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--text);}

  /* token colors */
  .k{color:var(--neon-magenta);}      /* keyword */
  .s{color:var(--neon-lime);}         /* string */
  .c{color:var(--text-dim);font-style:italic;} /* comment */
  .f{color:var(--neon-cyan);}         /* func/attr */
  .n{color:var(--neon-amber);}        /* number/const */
  .hl{
    background:rgba(157,255,60,0.10);
    border-left:2px solid var(--neon-lime);
    display:block;
    margin:0 -22px;
    padding:0 22px 0 20px;
    animation:flash 1s ease;
  }
  @keyframes flash{from{background:rgba(157,255,60,0.35);}to{background:rgba(157,255,60,0.10);}}

  /* ---------- BEFORE / FAILURE ---------- */
  .fail{
    border:1px solid var(--danger);
    background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,59,107,0.06), transparent);
    padding:18px 22px;
    margin:22px 0;
    box-shadow:inset 0 0 20px rgba(255,59,107,0.05);
  }
  .fail .label{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.2rem;
    color:var(--danger);
    letter-spacing:2px;
    text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(255,59,107,0.6);
    margin-bottom:6px;
  }
  .fail ul{list-style:none;}
  .fail li{padding-left:22px;position:relative;font-size:0.88rem;margin:6px 0;color:var(--text);}
  .fail li::before{content:"✗";position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--danger);}

  /* ---------- BUILD EXERCISE ---------- */
  .builder{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
    gap:22px;
    margin-top:30px;
    align-items:start;
  }
  @media(max-width:860px){.builder{grid-template-columns:1fr;}}

  .steps-col{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px;}
  .step{
    border:1px solid var(--panel-line);
    background:var(--panel);
    padding:16px 18px;
    opacity:0.4;
    filter:grayscale(0.6);
    transition:all .35s ease;
    position:relative;
  }
  .step.active{
    opacity:1;
    filter:none;
    border-color:var(--neon-cyan);
    box-shadow:0 0 18px rgba(25,240,255,0.18);
  }
  .step.done{opacity:0.85;border-color:var(--neon-lime);}
  .step .sn{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.3rem;
    color:var(--neon-cyan);
    letter-spacing:2px;
  }
  .step.done .sn{color:var(--neon-lime);}
  .step h4{font-size:0.92rem;color:#fff;margin:2px 0 6px;}
  .step p{font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--text-dim);}
  .step .chk{
    position:absolute;top:14px;right:16px;
    font-family:var(--crt);font-size:1.1rem;color:var(--neon-lime);
    opacity:0;transition:opacity .3s;
  }
  .step.done .chk{opacity:1;}

  .panel-col{position:sticky;top:20px;}
  .live-code{
    border:1px solid var(--neon-cyan);
    background:var(--bg);
    box-shadow:0 0 26px rgba(25,240,255,0.12);
    min-height:340px;
  }
  .live-code .code-bar{border-bottom-color:#1d3a4a;}
  .live-code pre{min-height:300px;}
  .empty-state{
    color:var(--text-dim);
    font-style:italic;
    padding:20px 0;
  }

  .controls{
    display:flex;
    gap:12px;
    margin-top:22px;
    flex-wrap:wrap;
  }
  button{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.25rem;
    letter-spacing:2px;
    padding:10px 22px;
    background:transparent;
    color:var(--neon-lime);
    border:1px solid var(--neon-lime);
    cursor:pointer;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    transition:all .18s;
    text-shadow:0 0 8px rgba(157,255,60,0.4);
  }
  button:hover:not(:disabled){
    background:var(--neon-lime);
    color:var(--bg-deep);
    box-shadow:0 0 22px rgba(157,255,60,0.5);
    text-shadow:none;
  }
  button.ghost{color:var(--text-dim);border-color:var(--panel-line);text-shadow:none;}
  button.ghost:hover:not(:disabled){background:var(--panel-line);color:var(--text);box-shadow:none;}
  button:disabled{opacity:0.3;cursor:not-allowed;}

  .progress{
    font-family:var(--crt);
    font-size:1.2rem;
    color:var(--neon-amber);
    letter-spacing:2px;
    margin-left:auto;
    align-self:center;
  }

  /* ---------- DIAGRAM ---------- */
  .diagram{margin:30px 0;display:flex;justify-content:center;}
  .diagram svg{max-width:100%;height:auto;}

  /* ---------- RECAP ---------- */
  .recap{
    margin-top:30px;
    border:1px solid var(--neon-amber);
    background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,182,39,0.05), transparent);
    padding:26px 28px;
    box-shadow:0 0 26px rgba(255,182,39,0.1);
  }
  .recap h3{
    font-family:var(--crt);font-size:1.6rem;color:var(--neon-amber);
    letter-spacing:2px;text-shadow:0 0 10px rgba(255,182,39,0.5);margin-bottom:14px;
  }
  .recap ul{list-style:none;}
  .recap li{padding-left:26px;position:relative;margin:12px 0;font-size:0.92rem;}
  .recap li::before{content:"▸";position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--neon-amber);font-size:1.1rem;}
  .recap b{color:var(--neon-cyan);}

  footer{
    margin-top:70px;padding-top:24px;border-top:1px solid var(--panel-line);
    color:var(--text-dim);font-size:0.78rem;text-align:center;letter-spacing:1px;
  }

  .glow-cy{color:var(--neon-cyan);}
  .glow-mg{color:var(--neon-magenta);}
  .glow-lm{color:var(--neon-lime);}
</style>

<script is:inline>
(function(){
  // Each step's code as an array of HTML lines (highlighted). Cumulative build.
  // We store full snapshots so each "add" shows the loop in its current assembled form.
  const snapshots = [
    // STEP 0: seed
`<span class="c"># STEP 1 — seed the conversation</span>
messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]`,

    // STEP 1: open loop
`messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]

<span class="hl"><span class="c"># STEP 2 — Pillar 01: one call is a dead end, so loop</span></span>
<span class="hl"><span class="k">while</span> <span class="k">True</span>:</span>
<span class="hl">    resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(</span>
<span class="hl">        model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,</span>
<span class="hl">        max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>, tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,</span>
<span class="hl">        <span class="c"># send full history</span></span>
<span class="hl">        messages<span class="k">=</span>messages,</span>
<span class="hl">    )</span>`,

    // STEP 2: inspect stop_reason
`messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]

<span class="k">while</span> <span class="k">True</span>:
    resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(
        model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,
        max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>, tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,
        messages<span class="k">=</span>messages,
    )
<span class="hl">    messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"assistant"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: resp.content})</span>
<span class="hl"></span>
<span class="hl">    <span class="c"># STEP 3 — Pillar 02</span></span>
<span class="hl">    <span class="k">if</span> resp.stop_reason <span class="k">!=</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:</span>
<span class="hl">        <span class="c"># end_turn = done, exit</span></span>
<span class="hl">        <span class="k">return</span> resp</span>`,

    // STEP 3: execute tool
`messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]

<span class="k">while</span> <span class="k">True</span>:
    resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(
        model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,
        max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>, tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,
        messages<span class="k">=</span>messages,
    )
    messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"assistant"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: resp.content})

    <span class="k">if</span> resp.stop_reason <span class="k">!=</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
        <span class="k">return</span> resp

<span class="hl">    <span class="c"># STEP 4 — you run the tool</span></span>
<span class="hl">    tool_results <span class="k">=</span> []</span>
<span class="hl">    <span class="k">for</span> block <span class="k">in</span> resp.content:</span>
<span class="hl">        <span class="k">if</span> block.type <span class="k">==</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:</span>
<span class="hl">            output <span class="k">=</span> <span class="f">execute_tool</span>(block.name, block.input)</span>`,

    // STEP 4: feed back
`messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]

<span class="k">while</span> <span class="k">True</span>:
    resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(
        model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,
        max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>, tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,
        messages<span class="k">=</span>messages,
    )
    messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"assistant"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: resp.content})

    <span class="k">if</span> resp.stop_reason <span class="k">!=</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
        <span class="k">return</span> resp

    tool_results <span class="k">=</span> []
    <span class="k">for</span> block <span class="k">in</span> resp.content:
        <span class="k">if</span> block.type <span class="k">==</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
            output <span class="k">=</span> <span class="f">execute_tool</span>(block.name, block.input)
<span class="hl">            <span class="c"># STEP 5 — Pillar 03</span></span>
<span class="hl">            tool_results.<span class="f">append</span>({</span>
<span class="hl">                <span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"tool_result"</span>,</span>
<span class="hl">                <span class="s">"tool_use_id"</span>: block.id,</span>
<span class="hl">                <span class="s">"content"</span>: output,</span>
<span class="hl">            })</span>
<span class="hl"></span>
<span class="hl">    messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: tool_results})</span>`,

    // STEP 5: backstop (convert while True -> for range)
`<span class="k">def</span> <span class="f">run_agent</span>(user_message, max_iterations<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">10</span>):
    messages <span class="k">=</span> [{<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: user_message}]

<span class="hl">    <span class="c"># STEP 6 — Pillar 04 backstop</span></span>
<span class="hl">    <span class="k">for</span> _ <span class="k">in</span> <span class="f">range</span>(max_iterations):</span>
        resp <span class="k">=</span> client.messages.<span class="f">create</span>(
            model<span class="k">=</span><span class="s">"claude-opus-4-8"</span>,
            max_tokens<span class="k">=</span><span class="n">1024</span>, tools<span class="k">=</span>tools,
            messages<span class="k">=</span>messages,
        )
        messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"assistant"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: resp.content})

        <span class="k">if</span> resp.stop_reason <span class="k">!=</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
            <span class="k">return</span> resp

        tool_results <span class="k">=</span> []
        <span class="k">for</span> block <span class="k">in</span> resp.content:
            <span class="k">if</span> block.type <span class="k">==</span> <span class="s">"tool_use"</span>:
                output <span class="k">=</span> <span class="f">execute_tool</span>(block.name, block.input)
                tool_results.<span class="f">append</span>({
                    <span class="s">"type"</span>: <span class="s">"tool_result"</span>,
                    <span class="s">"tool_use_id"</span>: block.id,
                    <span class="s">"content"</span>: output,
                })

        messages.<span class="f">append</span>({<span class="s">"role"</span>: <span class="s">"user"</span>, <span class="s">"content"</span>: tool_results})

<span class="hl">    <span class="c"># net fired</span></span>
<span class="hl">    <span class="k">raise</span> <span class="f">RuntimeError</span>(<span class="s">"Hit cap without end_turn"</span>)</span>`,
  ];

  const TOTAL = snapshots.length; // 6
  let current = 0; // number of steps added (0..6)

  const liveCode = document.getElementById('liveCode');
  const addBtn   = document.getElementById('addBtn');
  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn');
  const progress = document.getElementById('progress');
  const steps    = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.step'));

  function render(){
    progress.textContent = current + ' / ' + TOTAL;

    if(current === 0){
      liveCode.innerHTML = '<span class="empty-state c"># Empty. Click ADD STEP to begin assembling the loop...</span>';
    } else {
      liveCode.innerHTML = snapshots[current - 1];
    }

    steps.forEach((s,i)=>{
      s.classList.remove('active','done');
      if(i < current) s.classList.add('done');
      if(i === current) s.classList.add('active');
    });

    addBtn.disabled   = current >= TOTAL;
    addBtn.textContent = current >= TOTAL ? '✓ Complete' : '+ Add Step ' + (current + 1);
  }

  addBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=>{
    if(current < TOTAL){ current++; render(); }
  });
  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', ()=>{ current = 0; render(); });

  // init: mark first step active
  render();
})();
</script>
